Thus, by uniqueness, \chi _{m} =  \chi _{n}. Conversely, if \chi _{m} =  \chi _{n} then both m and n are isomorphic to the canonical pullback \chi _{m} ^{*} ( \top ). Thus, m  \cong  n.

